headline: US airlines' premium travel strategy is paying off amid demand slump
summary: The strategy is paying off as the margins of carriers selling premium seats have held up despite a slump in overall travel demand.  Delta Air Lines last week reported a 5% year-on-year jump in its second-quarter premium ticket revenue, compared to a 5% decline in main cabin revenue.  Similarly, premium cabin revenue helped United Airlines mitigate the financial hit from operational constraints at Newark airport near New York City - one of its largest hubs - and increase its earnings in the latest quarter.
